        <div class="place">
        <h2><strong>Leh</strong></h2>
            <img src="leh.jpg" alt="Leh">
            <p>
Leh-Ladakh is a mesmerizing region in the northernmost part of India, nestled within the Himalayan and Karakoram mountain ranges. Known for its breathtaking landscapes, high mountain passes, and distinctive culture, Leh-Ladakh has become a popular destination for adventure seekers and nature enthusiasts.</p>
        <p><strong>Explore Nature's Masterpieces</strong></p>
        <ul class="list">
        <li>Pangong Lake: Mesmerizing hues, towering mountains.</li>
        <li>Nubra Valley: Surreal beauty, sand dunes, snow-capped peaks.</li>
        <li>Magnetic Hill: Gravity-defying phenomenon.</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>Immerse in Culture and History</strong></p>
        <ul class="list">
        <li>Thiksey Monastery: Spiritual ambiance, hilltop, vibrant murals.</li>
        <li>Hemis Monastery: Largest in Ladakh, annual Hemis Festival.</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>Thrilling Adventures Await</strong></p>
        <ul class="list">
        <li>Trekking: Markha Valley Trek and other exhilarating trails.</li>
        <li>River Rafting: Conquer Zanskar River's rapids.</li>
        <li>Biking Expeditions: Navigate challenging roads on a thrilling motorcycle.</li>
        </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="place">
            <h2><strong>Pahalgam: Himalayan Gem</strong></h2>
            <img src="Pahalgam.jpg" alt="Pahalgam">
           <p>Nestled in Jammu and Kashmir, Pahalgam is a picturesque town on the Lidder River. Known for Betaab Valley's green expanse and the adventure hub of Aru Valley, it's a haven for nature lovers. Beyond its breathtaking landscapes, Pahalgam is a spiritual base for the Amarnath Yatra. In every season, Pahalgam captivates with its serene charm and adventure offerings, making it a Himalayan gem.</p>
<ul class="list">
        <li><strong>Location: </strong>Anantnag district of the union territory of Jammu and Kashmir, India.</li>
        </ul>
        </div>



        <div class="place">
            <h2><strong>Gulmarg: Alpine Wonderland</strong></h2>
            <img src="img3.jpg" alt="Gulmarg">
            <p>Nestled in the Pir Panjal range, Gulmarg in Jammu and Kashmir is a winter wonderland renowned for its pristine snow, making it a premier skiing destination. Home to one of the world's highest golf courses and the Gulmarg Gondola, the highest cable car, it offers breathtaking views of the snow-capped Himalayas. Beyond winter, Gulmarg transforms into a lush meadow, making it a year-round haven for nature enthusiasts and adventure seekers.</p>
            <ul class="list">
        <li><strong>Location: </strong> Pir Panjal range in the Union Territory of Jammu and Kashmir, India.</li>
        </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="place">
            <h2><strong>Pangong Lake: Turquoise Tranquility</strong></h2>
            <img src="pangong.jpg" alt="PangonLake">
                <p>Located at an elevation of 4,350 meters in Ladakh, Pangong Lake is a mesmerizing high-altitude wonder. The lake's expansive azure waters against a backdrop of rugged mountains create a breathtaking panorama. Its unique feature lies in the ever-changing hues, casting an enchanting spell on visitors. A visit to Pangong Lake offers a serene escape into the lap of nature, where tranquility and scenic beauty converge in perfect harmony.</p>
            <ul class="list">
        <li><strong>Location: </strong> Himalayan region of Ladakh, in the Union Territory of Jammu and Kashmir, India.</li>
        </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="place">
            <h2><strong>Zanskar Valley: The Hidden Himalayan Gem</strong></h2>
            <img src="zanskar.jpg" alt="Zanskar Valley">
            <p>Tucked away in the remote reaches of Ladakh, Zanskar Valley is a pristine Himalayan sanctuary. Enclosed by towering snow-capped peaks, this secluded haven offers a unique blend of ancient monasteries, frozen rivers, and traditional Ladakhi culture. Accessible only during certain months, Zanskar captivates with its untouched beauty and adventurous spirit, making it a cherished destination for those seeking the road less traveled in the Himalayas.</p>
            <ul class="list">
        <li><strong>Location: </strong>Ladakh, Jammu and Kashmir, India</li>
        </ul>
